extends ../layouts/default

block head
  title Accessible Times is Running

block neck
  link(rel='stylesheet', href='/views/index.min.css?#{cacheBreaker}')

block body
  div.jumbotron
    h1 Accessible Times
    p.lead
      | I spent some time working on this application that would be helpful to older folk, including my mother. This website/application lets people who are older regain access to information not available
      to older folk either due to age or expressive Aphasia. Here's how this works. One or more people (like my sister or I) can enter articles from across the net into the administration page. This site turns the article referenced by the button on the left into an article referenced in the button on the right. 
    p
      | Below is a simple proof of concept. On the left, a New York Times article. On the right, a more accessible version of the article. I hope that my mother will be able to check out the article on the right and at least hear the article, if not see it. I plan on making updates based on her feedback and the feedback of others.
      div
        a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href='http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/13/us/politics/fbi-director-comey-speaks-frankly-about-police-view-of-blacks.html', target="_blank") Sample NY Times Article
        |  or&nbsp;
        a.btn.btn-warning.btn-lg(href='/articles/one-two/', target="_blank") Accessible version of Article
